This is a straightforward application of the filter axioms in a topological space. The key insight is that the collection of sets of the form `{x | p x ‚ąß q x ‚ą® p' x ‚ąß q' x}` forms a filter. Specifically, it's the intersection of the sets formed by `{p x ‚ąß q x}` and `{p' x ‚ąß q' x}`.

Let's think about how to prove this. We need to show that the set `{x | p x ‚ąß q x ‚ą® p' x ‚ąß q' x}` is in the filter `ūĚďĚ x`. By the definition of a filter, this means that for every set `U` in `ūĚďĚ x`, we have `U ‚äÜ {x | p x ‚ąß q x ‚ą® p' x ‚ąß q' x}`.

