- `hT : {x | p x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x`
- `hT' : {x | p' x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x`
- `hS : {x | q x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x`
- `hS' : {x | q' x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x`

And we want to prove `{x | p x ‚ąß q x ‚ą® p' x ‚ąß q' x} ‚ąą ūĚďĚ x`.

Applying `filter_upwards` to these four hypotheses would transform the goal into:
`‚ąÄ x, x ‚ąą {x | p x} ‚Üí x ‚ąą {x | q x} ‚Üí x ‚ąą {x | p' x} ‚Üí x ‚ąą {x | q' x} ‚Üí x ‚ąą {x | p x ‚ąß q x ‚ą® p' x ‚ąß q' x}`

But this is exactly what we need. For any `x` that is in all four sets, we need to show it's in the union set.

