### 1. Monotonicity of Filter Maps

The first lemma to prove is `mono`, which states that if `F ‚Č§ G`, then `F.map f ‚Č§ G.map f` for a function `f : őĪ ‚Üí ő≤`. This is a standard property of filters and their maps. To prove this, we need to show that every set in `F.map f` is also in `G.map f`.

